  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was conducted informally across the five flow-speed operating points to confirm monotonic hemolysis trends; this screening confirmed that results are robust to minor inlet boundary condition perturbations. No structured uncertainty quantification propagation was deemed necessary given the relative hemolysis index (RH) acceptance criterion and the conservative nature of the worst-case operating point selection.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-cfd-credible",
